}

docs {
  # $translate-batch — 50 probes in one request

  50 (system, code) probes against the same ConceptMap. On the server side
  this collapses to **one** `unnest WITH ORDINALITY` JOIN against
  `concept_map_mappings` — see `postgres.MappingStore.BatchQueryForward`.

  Compare with calling `$translate` 50 times:
  - 50 HTTP requests vs 1
  - 50 SQL roundtrips vs 1
  - 50 ConceptMap-by-URL resolutions vs 1
  - 50 request_id allocations + 50 log lines vs 1

  For an ETL job translating millions of codes against a stable ConceptMap,
  this is the difference between a 10-minute job and an 8-hour one.
}
